OL,6,FBut he said the company refused to
OL,7,Fmake the investments necessary to
OL,8,Fprovide for the animals' basic care.
OL,10,FCages were cleaned twice a month
OL,11,Frather than every day as required.
OL,12,FAnimals were euthanised, including by
OL,13,Fdirect injections to their heart,
OL,14,Fwithout sedation, he said.
OL,16,FDogs were routinely injured by getting
OL,17,Ftheir paws caught in flooring composed
OL,18,Fof metal grates that left space for
OL,19,Fpaws to easily fall through.
